# Chat Router

Keep one production chat router: `services/zoe-data/routers/chat.py`. Do not create `chat_v2.py`, `_new`, `_fixed`, or side routers for production behavior.

Natural-language handling should live in `intent_router.py` or Zoe Agent (Hermes/OpenClaw are retirement targets — never destinations). Avoid adding broad hardcoded phrase branches in `chat.py`; use focused intents for stable fast paths and agent routing for fuzzy language.

Every new feature reachable from chat/voice needs:
- An intent or agent/tool path.
- A useful inline response or AG-UI card, not just a URL.
- A backend status endpoint when it is an integration.
- A settings or feature UI section where appropriate.

Preserve AG-UI SSE event patterns already used in `chat.py`. Persist user/assistant turns and run memory extraction through existing hooks so chat, voice, and nightly digest stay consistent.

For complex repair or development tasks, follow the Flue executor migration plan. OpenClaw is being FULLY RETIRED (operator decision 2026-07-22) — do not route work to it or preserve it in deletion PRs.
